    <p>
      <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_hyperbaric_oxygen_therapy">Hyperbaric Oxygen Therapy</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_clinical_intervention">CLINICAL INTERVENTION</xref>.        </p>
    <p>
      <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_hyperbaric_oxygen_therapy">Hyperbaric Oxygen Therapy</xref>
 (<xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_hyperbaric_oxygen_therapy">HBOT</xref>), also known as 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_hyperbaric_oxygen_therapy">Hyperbaric Medicine</xref>, involves breathing pure oxygen at higher than atmospheric pressures in an enclosed chamber.        </p>
    <p>
For further information on 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_hyperbaric_oxygen_therapy">Hyperbaric Oxygen Therapy</xref>, see the 
              <xref href="https://www.cancer.gov/dictionary?CdrID=45218" scope="external" format="html">National Cancer Institute website</xref>.        </p>
